cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on measuring the data-freshness performance of a status update system, which is related to the concept of age of information (AoI) in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with enabling applications in massive IoT, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper formulates the system as two queues and considers different service disciplines, which are related to the concepts of queuing theory and control theory. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems): The paper deals with optimizing the performance of a status update system, which can be seen as a multiagent system with multiple components interacting with each other. 
5. cs.PF (Performance): The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of the status update system in terms of data-freshness and penalty, which is related to the concept of performance evaluation in computer systems.
